## Experiment: `2026-06-04-stability-heterophily-regime`

### Code Changes Made

**`scripts/run_adaptive_grage_search.py`** — three additions:

1. **Clean noise handling** in `run_experiment_matrix()` (line ~910): when `noise_type == "clean"`, skips `inject_noise()` and uses the original graph edges with an all-false `bad_edge_mask`. This lets us test on the pristine heterophily graph without noise injection.

2. **`get_heterophily_methods()`** (line ~1408): returns 6 method configs + Random-Matched (handled inline):
   - Feature-only
   - GCN-Jaccard
   - DegreeAwareRandom
   - MCGC-cw3.0-lp0.1-ln0.5
   - GraGE-Hybrid-FO-posneg-lp0.1-ln0.5
   - StabilityResidual-v5-dp0.15-grad-frozen (selected candidate)

3. **`run_heterophily()`** (line ~1452): runs the matrix over:
   - Datasets: Texas, Wisconsin, Actor
   - Noise types: `feature_similar_cross_class`, `low_feature_similarity`, `degree_aligned_random`, `clean`
   - 10 seeds per dataset
   - `stability_heterophily` mode added to argparser and main dispatch

### Matrix Size

3 datasets × 4 noise types × 10 seeds × 7 methods = **840 total runs**

Texas/Wisconsin are small (~183/251 nodes), so those will be fast. Actor (7600 nodes, 53k edges) with StabilityResidual (5 GCN views) will be the bottleneck — roughly 3-5 min per StabilityResidual run on Actor.

